                    <div id="Marketing">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Hello</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">Welcome to the Easter edition of the Loop! We are delighted to bring you the latest news from across Reach Ireland. As we are preparing for upcoming award ceremonies, and the long weekend we have a lot to be excited about. This issue of the Loop includes highlights from our commercial team's wins and achievements, updates from circulation and production, and a special 5 minutes with Ryan Smith, our editor at IrishStar. Our team in Belfast has been nominated for an award, and our Belfast and Dublin hubs are full of Easter cheer! So, join us as we celebrate the successes of the past quarter, and let us know what else you would like to see us cover by emailing  <a href="mailto:theloopireland@reachplc.com" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>theloopireland@reachplc.com</b></a>. <br>Don't forget to share your Easter photos with us, and have a safe and happy Easter!
</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="Marketing">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Marketing</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">Marketing kicked off Cheltenham with their fully integrated campaign across Ireland. They had print pocket guides, bumper preview magazines, daily pullouts & free bets with pre-promo print ads, radio campaigns, and social media campaigns. The live blogs, Robbie Power column, and Peter O'Hehir tips were all heavily promoted. The new horse racing newsletter gained 1,200 new subscribers during the festival. Digital display ads, web strips, Facebook ads, re-engagement campaigns, cross-promotional emails, and a competition to win an overnight stay in Dublin City Centre with access to the Paddy Power Fanzone all helped to boost subscriptions. It's safe to say that Cheltenham was a great success!
</p>
             <img src=https://github.com/jamesleahyreachplc/TheLoop/blob/April-Loop/Marketing%204.JPG?raw=true style="width:48%;margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;">
