          </div>          
          <div id="Circulation">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Circulation</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">Our biggest week of the year is in March and we sold in excess of 90k extra papers week on week across our three daily titles during Cheltenham. But even with this success, the February issue of RSVP still closed at 17,507 - not an easy feat in the current cost of living crisis. Our competitors, such as VIP, Stellar, and Irish Country magazine, have also experienced heavy sales decreases this month. 
<br>April looks to be packed with newsworthy events, from the visits of two Presidents to the Hutch trial resuming and anniversaries of the Good Friday Agreement. We also have three major racing festivals - the Irish Grand National, Aintree Grand National, and Punchestown - to look forward to at the end of the month.
</p>             
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="Digital">
            <div id="myHeader" style="background-color: #fed780;padding: 20px;margin: 10px;">
              <h1 style="color: #3D5161;margin-top: 0px;font-family: Tahoma;">Digital</h1>
              <p style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;">Our US team is now fully in place across the pond and already flying with the <a href="https://www.irishstar.com/" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>IrishStar.com</b></a> surpassing the 1 million page view mark in its first full month. At home, it was a record-breaking month for <a href="https://www.buzz.ie/" style="color: #3D5161;font-family: Tahoma;"><b>Buzz.ie</b></a> made even more impressive due to the small team. Mark Kavanagh moves to steer that ship from the first week of April. March was also a fruitful month for Belfast, Cork and RSVP, despite Facebook's best efforts to stop us in our tracks.
</p>
   </div>
